# systemd-journal-upload pushes journal entries over HTTPS to a remote
# systemd-journal-remote receiver. Native systemd, smallest footprint.
# Caveat: NOT interoperable with Graylog / Splunk / rsyslog as a sender —
# the receiver must be systemd-journal-remote.
# Configure URL in overlay/etc/systemd/journal-upload.conf (TODO).

systemd-journal-remote
